{"id": 223711604, "title": "Warning over pensioners mugged with 'lion killer' jiu-jitsu move in Benidorm", "text": "The two men have been arrested for the crime (Picture: Shutterstock) Police in Benidorm have arrested two men they caught robbing a British pensioner by using a martial art stranglehold. Undercover cops nabbed the pair after seeing them assaulting the pensioner in broad daylight in the famous Costa Blanca resort and trying to leave him unconscious with the popular choke used in Brazilian Jiu Jitsu. Violent street muggers are increasingly using the technique, which in Brazil is known as Mata leao, \u2018lion killer\u2019 in English, to incapacitate their victims. A spokesman for the National Police at the force\u2019s provincial HQ in Alicante said: \u2018Officers have arrested two men in Benidorm who were caught as they committed a violent robbery in broad daylight in a busy central street. \u2018The officers were carrying out routine undercover patrol work and saw the two detainees pulling and hitting an elderly British man. \u2018The assault continued with them grabbing their victim round the neck and using the martial arts Mata leao chokehold to try to leave him unconscious so they could rob him. The pensioner was taken for treatment (Picture: Shutterstock) The pensioner suffered a cut to head when the two men dropped him after seeing the police. The two muggers were arrested near the scene and police recovered the man\u2019s wallet. They added: \u2018He was taken to a medical centre to receive treatment. The men arrested are Spaniards aged 47 and 48 who have been arrested before for similar offences. \u2018They have been handed over to the judiciary ahead of their court appearance.\u2019 It was not immediately clear today if they have already appeared before a judge and whether they have been remanded in custody or released on bail. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.", "summary": "The two muggers were arrested near the scene and police recovered the man's wallet.", "url": "https://metro.co.uk/2024/05/26/warning-pensioners-mugged-lion-killer-jiu-jitsu-move-benidorm-20913425/", "image": "https://metro.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/SEI_203299583-4448.jpg?quality=90&strip=all", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 14:05:21", "author": "Sarah Hooper", "authors": ["Sarah Hooper"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.052}